
[1]appanage

   AP'PANAGE, n.

   1. Lands appropriated by a prince to the maintenance of his younger
   sons, as their patrimony; but on condition of the failure of male
   offspring, they were to revert to the donor or his heir. From the
   appanage it was customary for the sons to take their surnames.

   2. Sustenance; means of nourishing.

   Wealth - the appanage of wit.
